## Building on Yesterday's Foundation

Day 27 established the concept of common controls and mapped out which AWS infrastructure controls OpenMRS inherits automatically. Today I went a level deeper — looking at the specific AWS security services that function as enterprise-wide common controls, and exploring how a Security Operations Center fits into the picture for an organization like MyClinic.

The theme that kept coming up today is the difference between having security tools available and actually integrating them into a functioning security program. AWS offers powerful native security services. But they do not configure themselves, they do not respond to alerts on their own, and they do not replace the need for people and processes. Understanding what each tool does — and what it does not do — is what makes the difference between a security posture that looks good on paper and one that actually works.

